MemberSignature.Value: public: property bool AutoLoad { bool get(); void set(bool value); };

summary.span: 如果打开包含指定 OLE 对象的工作簿时自动载入该 OLE 对象，则为 True。Boolean 类型，可读写。

span.span: True if the OLE object is automatically loaded when the workbook that contains it is opened. Read/write Boolean.

span.para: ActiveX 控件，则忽略此属性。打开工作簿时，始终进行加载 ActiveX 控件。
对于大多数 OLE 对象类型，此属性不应设置为True。默认情况下AutoLoad属性设置为False的新的 OLE 对象;Microsoft Excel 加载工作簿时，此节省时间和内存。自动加载 OLE 对象，表示可变数据的对象，可以立即重新建立链接到源数据和对象可以再次呈现，如有必要。
This property is ignored by ActiveX controls. ActiveX controls are always loaded when a workbook is opened.

For most OLE object types, this property shouldn’t be set to True. By default, the AutoLoad property is set to False for new OLE objects; this saves time and memory when Microsoft Excel is loading workbooks. The benefit of automatically loading OLE objects is that, for objects that represent volatile data, links to source data can be reestablished immediately and the objects can be rendered again if necessary.

Setting this property to 0 (zero) will make the window a tiny bit smaller than it would be if the application window were maximized.
